article.headline: Siena 92, Rider 73
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. (AP) -- Kenny Hasbrouck scored 22 points -- one of five Siena players in double figures -- to lead the Saints to a 92-73 win over Rider on Sunday. Kojo Mensah, Antoine Jordan and Tay Fischer each had 17 points for Siena (12-11, 7-8 in Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference), while Mike Beers added 12 points and four steals. Terrance Mouton and Jason Thompson each had 17 points for Rider (8-15, 4-11), which had a tough night from the floor, hitting just 39 percent of their shots. Sienna, which never trailed, took command early and held double-digit leads for most of the game. The Saints started the game with a 22-5 run, including 12 points from Fischer, and their defense kept Rider off-balance for most of the day. The Broncs tried to rally midway through the second half with a 12-4 run that cut the Saints lead to seven points, but Sienna soon sealed the win with an 18-2 run. Mensah, who scored six points during that stretch, also finished with a game-high nine rebounds.
